
TOPIC: MAP/BLIM

650          028A          BLIM

Cassette data record buffer size;
contains the number of active data
bytes in the cassette buffer for the
record being read or written, at
location 1021 ($3FD). Values range
from zero to 128 (cassette record size
is 128; $80). The pointer to the byte
being read or written is at 61 ($3D).
The value of BLIM is drawn from the
control bytes that precede every
cassette record, as explained in
location 1021.

